Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.05,0:00:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Archbishop.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.09,0:00:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I asked thee not to call me via that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.16,0:00:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here without an escort?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.74,0:00:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you finish this business at the St. George Cathedral?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.98,0:00:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldst not be trapped in that old cathedral all year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.07,0:00:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we can converse while walking, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.15,0:00:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.26,0:00:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're very narrow-minded, Stiyl.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.87,0:00:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Canst thou not simply enjoy the fact that\Nthou art walking with someone like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.90,0:00:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Laura Stuart, may I ask you a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.40,0:00:42.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, how formal. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.71,0:00:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you talking in such a stupid way?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.08,0:00:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Dost it sound strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.79,0:00:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I even had a real Japanese person check it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.27,0:00:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And who might that have been?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.03,0:01:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He goes by the name of Tsuchimikado Motoharu.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.18,0:01:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't use that man as an example of a normal Japanese person!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.16,0:01:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A communication talisman?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.45,0:01:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know about The Book of the Law, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.62,0:01:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A grimoire?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember correctly, the author was Edward Alexander.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.59,0:01:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was originally found in the The Roman Church's Vatican Library.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.64,0:01:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, no one was able to decipher it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.80,0:01:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Index, who contains 103,000 volumes?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.02,0:01:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you say if someone who could read The Book of the Law were to appear?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.78,0:01:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.04,0:01:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a Roman Catholic Sister by the name of Orsola Aquinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.92,0:01:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do they plan on using The Book of the Law as a method of regaining their power?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.59,0:02:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You needn't worry about that. At least not for now...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.75,0:02:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because both the The Book of the Law and Orsola Aquinas have been stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.00,0:02:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we discuss more about this inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.93,0:02:37.01,TOARUnextepisode,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(670,0)\fs70.5\pos(549,652)\c&H821213&\fsp-2}To{\fsp-7}a{\fsp0}ru Ma{\fsp-7}j{\fsp-7}u{\fsp-7}t{\fsp-4}s{\fsp-2}u no {\fsp-4}I{\fsp-2}n{\fsp-4}d{\fsp-4}e{\fsp-2}x
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.36,0:03:51.44,TOARUepisodetitle,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(670,670)\bord2.5\fs40\pos(1047,576)}The {\fsp-2}Book\Nof the {\fsp-3}La{\fsp0}w
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.62,0:03:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second semester is really busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.34,0:04:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's full of festivals like Daihaseisai, Ichihanaransai,\NArt Appreciation Festival, and Social Studies Field Trip Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.79,0:04:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sphinx, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.93,0:04:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I still have a lot of free time!\NThere's nothing to do! I'm so bored!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.17,0:04:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Touma won't play with me at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.06,0:04:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamijou Touma has his own life to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.92,0:04:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like he wants to be in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.34,0:04:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why aren't you in school, Maika?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.04,0:04:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.38,0:04:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, it's quite normal for a maid to train in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.68,0:04:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll become a maid too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.44,0:04:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe I'll go play with Touma during class!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.98,0:04:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The life of a maid is not an easy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.53,0:04:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be especially difficult for a girl with zero domestic skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.94,0:04:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Touma can be the maid!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.09,0:04:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, Touma can come play with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.34,0:04:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For Kamijou Touma's sake,\Nyou probably shouldn't suggest that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.93,0:05:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.57,0:05:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.84,0:05:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems that there is no time for either you or him to become maids.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.05,0:05:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Daihaseisai."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.05,0:05:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A large sports festival that every school in Academy City participates in."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.38,0:05:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"In order to observe the large-scale interference between espers,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.47,0:05:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"students are encouraged to use their powers to the fullest on this day."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.00,0:05:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.92,0:05:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, Kamijou Touma, have lost my memories due to certain circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.69,0:05:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, I remember absolutely nothing concerning this big event.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.03,0:06:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.45,0:06:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I make for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.33,0:06:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-K-K-Kamijou Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.27,0:06:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.21,0:06:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.07,0:06:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The silver-haired Sister was kidnapped by some guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.22,0:06:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.99,0:06:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a kidnapping! An abduction I tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.98,0:06:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.64,0:06:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.68,0:06:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As he left, the kidnapper gave me this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.84,0:06:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear Kamijou Touma,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.74,0:06:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you value her life, then tonight at seven, come to the\Nabandoned theater "Gloaming House" outside Academy City.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.06,0:06:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.18,0:06:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was this bastard like?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.21,0:06:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... well, he must have been over 180cm tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.59,0:06:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His hair was a dark red, and he had\Nsome kind of barcode under his right eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.70,0:07:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was smoking a cigarette, and he had lots of earrings on...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.86,0:07:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's fine, Maika.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.97,0:07:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Index and I both know the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.67,0:07:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know the culprit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.40,0:07:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So his motive for this is twisted love?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.46,0:07:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.24,0:07:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not quite...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.93,0:07:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An Exit... Permit...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.80,0:07:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you know most of what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.61,0:07:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Book of the Law has gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.12,0:07:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the only person capable of deciphering it, Orsola Aquinas, was also kidnapped, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.55,0:07:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And apparently the Amakusa Catholics are responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.39,0:07:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How on Earth was it taken from that unbelievably secure Vatican Library?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.78,0:07:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Roman Catholic Church was transporting\NThe Book of the Law to a Japanese museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.33,0:07:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could they just transport something so dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.08,0:08:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, is this why the Roman Catholic Church is requesting help from the Church of England?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.13,0:08:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.27,0:08:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a much bigger problem on our hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.06,0:08:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.31,0:08:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't been able to contact Kanzaki Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.39,0:08:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanzaki was formerly the top of the Amakusa Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.73,0:08:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she were to find out the Amakusa Church and the\NRoman Catholic Church have turned against each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to settle this mess before Kanzaki does anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.30,0:08:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By any means necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.83,0:08:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanzaki is a Saint, one of less than twenty in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.05,0:08:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you want me to fight her...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.81,0:08:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If such a need arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.86,0:08:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to go to Academy City first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.41,0:08:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Stiyl, take this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.69,0:08:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.76,0:09:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider it a small gift for Orsola.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.52,0:09:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And get in touch with Index.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.13,0:09:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need a specialist, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.63,0:09:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you dragging Touma into this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.94,0:09:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.60,0:09:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I have to work with him anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.98,0:09:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're going to go all the way to the Amakusa Church's base?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.64,0:09:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the circumstances have changed slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.88,0:09:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.54,0:09:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where could this "Gloaming House" be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.34,0:09:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the outside of Academy City at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.25,0:09:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.45,0:10:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me she's one of Index's acquaintances...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.89,0:10:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.13,0:10:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? Can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.62,0:10:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the bus to take if I'm heading to Academy City?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.24,0:10:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Academy City?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.96,0:10:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any buses that go to Academy City.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.53,0:10:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just buses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.93,0:10:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All forms of transportation from outside Academy City are cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.86,0:10:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gate's in that direction, so if you walk—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.20,0:10:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much for taking time\Nout of your busy schedule to assist me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.55,0:10:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just told you buses won't take you there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.39,0:10:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. You did say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.35,0:10:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, you walk in that direction\Nand enter through the gate over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.01,0:10:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.18,0:10:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for troubling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.69,0:10:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.98,0:10:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You're just blowing off\Neverything I say with a smile, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.42,0:11:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems as if something is irritating you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.62,0:11:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.19,0:11:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll excuse me, it seems that you're sweating quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.62,0:11:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.75,0:11:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, why are you going to Academy City?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.03,0:11:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.23,0:11:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm being pursued.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.33,0:11:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're being pursued?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.65,0:11:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The situation's a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.23,0:11:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our information's all over the place too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even know if we've secured The Book of the Law...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.59,0:11:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for my late introduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.50,0:11:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Agnese Sanctis from the Roman Catholic Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.09,0:11:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.70,0:11:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what kind of spell did the Amakusa Church use?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.23,0:11:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, we don't have a precise analysis of it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.59,0:12:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The special trait of the Amakusa Church is secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.14,0:12:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Amakusa Church doesn't use spells or magic circles plainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.59,0:12:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They hide all rituals and incantations in everyday actions and customs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.04,0:12:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even professional magicians cannot discern their true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.68,0:12:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a bothersome bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.49,0:12:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.98,0:12:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola Aquinas!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.84,0:12:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.50,0:12:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you pretending to kidnap her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.56,0:12:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you saw right through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.84,0:12:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just going to have you\Nassist me in finding a missing individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.41,0:12:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finding someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.72,0:12:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.61,0:12:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, if you'd be so kind as to hand over that Sister standing beside you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.64,0:12:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like {\alphaFFF}I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.37,0:12:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I {\alphaFFF}said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.92,0:12:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:13:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Sister is the missing individual: Orsola Aquinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.12,0:13:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job. You're free to go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.86,0:13:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... what do I get in return for\Nwalking around in this blistering heat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.84,0:13:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I already thank you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.80,0:13:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, do you want me to treat you to some shaved ice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.44,0:13:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And here I was, thinking that I'd try to get along with you even if our personalities don't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.28,0:13:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Up until now, at least!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.77,0:13:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be you want me to care about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.74,0:13:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I cannot fill the empty sadness within you. Nor do I want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.25,0:13:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now hurry up and hand Orsola over to Agnese.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.64,0:13:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, you said that you were being pursued earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.60,0:13:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Orsola?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.23,0:13:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.43,0:13:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't just let you hand her over so easily, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.18,0:13:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola Aquinas...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.31,0:14:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can guarantee your life will be far more meaningful with the Amakusa Church than with the Roman Catholic Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.71,0:14:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Amakusa Church!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.56,0:14:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.44,0:14:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't, Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.34,0:14:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire is in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thy shape is a sword, and thy purpose is—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.76,0:14:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.03,0:14:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Stiyl, you'd better explain this\Nentire thing to me from beginning to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.52,0:14:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I could use an explanation, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.95,0:14:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Book of the Law is a grimoire\Nwritten in a code that nobody can decipher.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.45,0:14:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that you can attain tremendous power once you can decipher it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.05,0:14:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.95,0:14:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that book really that valuable?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.64,0:15:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rumor has it that the world ruled by Christian religion will come to an end if one were to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.65,0:15:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not just burn a book like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.69,0:15:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grimoires cannot be burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.94,0:15:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At best they can only be sealed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.56,0:15:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.32,0:15:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to start by explaining the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.11,0:15:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.40,0:15:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.27,0:15:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, stop! Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.40,0:15:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, don't you think you're going a little overboard with this prank?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.44,0:15:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop getting aroused during work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.62,0:16:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment, Orsola Aquinas is in the hands of the Amakusa Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.00,0:16:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We estimate fifty people from the Amakusa Church are involved in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.38,0:16:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a possibility that they might even be on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.86,0:16:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you don't know anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're tracking the movements of the\NAmakusa Church from their traces of magic, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.93,0:16:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Amakusa Church specializes in escaping and hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.16,0:16:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't catch them so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.53,0:16:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But there's no way they could get past our net.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.34,0:16:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Special Movement Method: Map Pilgrimage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.41,0:16:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This spell is limited to Japan only.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.56,0:16:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, there are forty-seven\Nspecial whirlpools spread across Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.17,0:16:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This "map magic" allows one to move freely between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.55,0:16:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all over for us if they jump using a whirlpool!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.30,0:16:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you taking your time for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.75,0:16:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because there's no need to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.92,0:16:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.44,0:16:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Map Pilgrimage is heavily dependent on the movement of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can only be used at a certain time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.63,0:17:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only time the special movement method can be used is directly after midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.53,0:17:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we have about four and a half hours left.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.10,0:17:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway... Touma, let me see that whatchamacallit, that map thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.01,0:17:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.18,0:17:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.82,0:17:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this net, there's only one whirlpool they can use.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.27,0:17:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.14,0:17:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.39,0:17:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything I can help out with?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.79,0:17:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times must I tell you to double-check your work?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.10,0:17:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes Ma'am. I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.23,0:17:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Sisters have it rough too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.36,0:17:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Index's tent...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.98,0:17:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? She's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.14,0:18:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh, where did she run off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.27,0:18:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.24,0:18:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Index!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.86,0:18:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Amakusa Church!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.46,0:18:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.67,0:18:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.58,0:18:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's just a slug.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.29,0:18:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Slug...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.83,0:18:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.62,0:18:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a hold of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.08,0:18:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.95,0:18:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... I-I just thought that the\NAmakusa Church was invading, and uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.19,0:18:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.07,0:18:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, calm down, Index...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.70,0:19:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't suit you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.23,0:19:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't usually act like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.27,0:19:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about just doing what you normally—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.54,0:19:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Stiyl...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.98,0:19:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.20,0:19:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm extremely irritated right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.08,0:19:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.35,0:19:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Stiyl?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.81,0:19:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The woman I respect is Elizabeth I, and my type is Saint Martha.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.46,0:19:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Amakusa Christian Church...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.12,0:19:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the one Kanzaki Kaori was in, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.29,0:19:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who did you hear that from?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.85,0:19:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsuchimikado?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.94,0:19:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that means the Amakusa Church\Nstill communicates with Kanzaki, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.89,0:19:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing that... are you still going to fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.84,0:19:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.92,0:20:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I've decided to do anything to protect that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.05,0:20:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means killing anyone in my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.59,0:20:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll burn them alive, and char their bodies if they're already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.02,0:20:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I vowed this a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.33,0:20:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that girl forgot everything,\NI won't forget anything that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.56,0:20:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it means putting my life on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.84,0:20:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to sleep already.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.51,0:20:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stiyl...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.10,0:20:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is still there, which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.43,0:20:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Stop that, Index!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.90,0:20:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, Touma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.14,0:20:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agnese?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.09,0:20:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.45,0:20:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.16,0:20:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.48,0:20:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.94,0:21:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And because it's a dream, I can bite Touma as much as I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.91,0:21:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can express all of my discontent!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.99,0:21:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, Index. This is undoubtedly real—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.57,0:21:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How unlucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.44,0:21:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Acting Pope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.92,0:21:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've completed preparations for the Map Pilgrimage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.77,0:21:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.20,0:21:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanzaki Kaori, I'll show you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.83,0:21:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the multi-religion incorporated Christian Church—the Amakusa Christian Church—looks like now!
